race.comment: LYLES (3) starting to live up to the big boom placed on him. Has monstered his rivals in two runs back, including a slick victory in fast time over 1000m at Eagle Farm. Likely to take control early and will prove hard to get past. SNACK BAR (7) consistent sprinter who resumes for the Bjorn Baker yard. Fitted with the two trials and can tag the fast tempo and play a leading role. KING'S SECRET (1) exciting gelding resuming. Should have little trouble in this company and comes to hand quickly. Has the two trials under his belt and saves his best for this track and trip. BREMEL (11) speedy mare who faces a few hurdles today up in class and trip. Tom Sherry retains the ride and has the speed to hold a forward position from the awkward gate. Place best. APEX (5) scored a strong win on resumption and not to be overlooked.
